-- GVT to Invest 300 Million Reais to Expand in Rio de Janeiro, O Globo Says
-- B y   L a u r a   P r i c e
-- 2010-10-12T09:10:38Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-12/gvt-to-invest-300-million-reais-to-expand-in-rio-de-janeiro-o-globo-says.html
GVT Holding SA , the Brazilian
telephone operator controlled by  Vivendi SA , plans to invest 300
million reais ($180 million) through 2012 to expand in Rio de
Janeiro city, O Globo reported, citing Alcides Troller Pinto,
marketing and sales director at GVT.  GVT will sell fixed-line telephone and broadband Internet
services in Rio, the newspaper said. The company wants to
compete with Tele Norte Leste Participacoes SA, known as Oi, and
Net Servicos de Comunicacao SA, Rio-based O Globo said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Laura Price at 
